<br>
So, I'm sure this info is buried SOMEWHERE on this board but I have no idea where to look or how far to dig so I'm just gonna ask - does anyone have any info or any good websites I can check to find out the exact scoop on this softcap I keep hearing about.<br>
<br>
From the in context usage of the term I gather it is the unbuffed AC total - sounds to me like going over 1250 AC at level 60 would not be beneficial in any way.  Also, I'm curious - is the 1250 cap supposed to be at your BASE agility ?  or at an agi of 1 ?  I mean, can you get your AC to 1250 at your base agi and then the extra AC you get from agi is considered a buff and does not apply to the softcap restriction?<br>
<br>
As you can see I have a lot of questions about it so any help would be greatly appreciated.<br>
<br>
Thanks a bunch guys.<br>
